Bangladesh has been authorized topurchase about 32,000 bales (480 lbs) of U.S. cotton under anexisting PL 480 agreement, the U.S. Agriculture Departmentsaid.    It may buy the cotton, valued at 10.0 mln dlrs, between May6 and August 15, 1987 and ship it by September 15, thedepartment said. Reuter&#3;